From c6d0aefd0d4c018d03697f1d867da3bac464fc9f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alex Goins <agoins@nvidia.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 2026 17:12:20 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] open-gpu-kernel-modules: Preview per-plane DRM color pipeline
 API in 595.58.03

This commit implements preview support for the upstream DRM per-plane
pre-blending color pipeline API in open-gpu-kernel-modules 595.58.03. Refer to
https://docs.kernel.org/gpu/rfc/color_pipeline.html for associated upstream
documentation.

Official support is planned for a future major-version driver release. This
commit, when based on top of 595.58.03, is intended primarily as a compositor
development vehicle.

The Turing+ color pipeline is exposed via colorops:

  * = "NVIDIA Full" and "NVIDIA FP Full" Only

  +-------------------------------+
  | FMT_CTM         [FMT]         |  CTM 3x4    (Intended for YUV->RGB)
  +-------------------------------+
  | DEGAMMA_TF      [ILUT]        |  1D Curve   (Named EOTF)
  | DEGAMMA_LUT     [ILUT]        |  1D LUT     (Custom EOTF LUT)
  | DEGAMMA_MULT    [ILUT]        |  Multiplier (Gain)
  +-------------------------------+
  | LMS_CTM*        [CSC00]       |  CTM 3x4    (Intended for RGB->LMS)
  +-------------------------------+
  | PQ_INV_EOTF*    [CSC0LUT]     |  1D Curve   (PQ Inverse EOTF, Non-bypassable)
  +-------------------------------+
  | LMS_TO_ITP_CTM* [CSC01]       |  CTM 3x4    (Intended for LMS->ICtCp)
  +-------------------------------+
  | TMO_LUT*        [TMO]         |  1D LUT     (Tone Mapping, R=G=B, Only remaps G)
  +-------------------------------+
  | ITP_TO_LMS_CTM* [CSC10]       |  CTM 3x4    (Intended for ICtCp->LMS)
  +-------------------------------+
  | PQ_EOTF*        [CSC1LUT]     |  1D Curve   (PQ EOTF, Non-bypassable)
  +-------------------------------+
  | BLEND_CTM       [CSC11]       |  CTM 3x4    (Intended for LMS->Blend)
  +-------------------------------+

Four pipeline variants are exposed:

  "NVIDIA Full"    - All operations (ICtCp TMO-capable planes only, Integer FB)
  "NVIDIA Lite"    - No ICtCp/TMO operations (Integer FB)
  "NVIDIA FP Full" - No ILUT operations (ICtCp TMO-capable planes only, FP FB)
  "NVIDIA FP Lite" - No ICtCp/TMO or ILUT operations (FP FB)

Due to known limitations of the upstream color pipeline API
(https://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/dri-devel/2024-September/469470.html),
there are a couple restrictions that can't be conveyed programmatically:

- No per-pipeline IN_FORMATS. All associated ILUT operations must be bypassed if
  a floating point FB is attached to a plane, or the atomic commit will fail.
  It is recommended for clients to use an "FP" pipeline variant if a floating
  point FB is in use.

- No single-channel LUT. The TMO LUT is represented using a generic 1D LUT, but
  the driver enforces R=G=B or the atomic commit will fail. Only 'G' is
  remapped.

Note also that due to hardware limitations, PQ_INV_EOTF (CSC0LUT) and PQ_EOTF
(CSC1LUT) cannot be bypassed without also bypassing all operations between them.
To convey this programmatically, these operations are marked as non-bypassable.
Clients that wish to bypass them should choose a "lite" pipeline variant.

As the upstream per-CRTC post-blending color pipeline API is not yet available,
clients must make use of the requisite vendor-specific operations for regamma:

  +-----------------------------------+
  | NV_CRTC_REGAMMA_TF       [OLUT]   |  enum      (Named Inverse EOTF)
  | NV_CRTC_REGAMMA_LUT      [OLUT]   |  blob      (Custom Inverse EOTF LUT)
  | NV_CRTC_REGAMMA_DIVISOR  [OLUT]   |  S31.32    (Divisor to re-normalize gain to 1.0)
  | NV_CRTC_REGAMMA_LUT_SIZE [OLUT]   |  immutable (Custom LUT Size)
  +-----------------------------------+

Signed-off-by: Alex Goins <agoins@nvidia.com>
